<table border='0' width='80%' height='674' cellpadding='5'>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0e024d'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>What
    are all these terms and abbreviations?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><ul>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>DoT</strong> - Damage over Time.&nbsp; Refers to those
        spells which do continuous damage (Suffocating Sphere, Choke, etc..)</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Buff</strong> - A spell which improves your character
        (Strength, Haze, Shielding, etc..)</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>DeBuff</strong> - The opposite of a buff that you cast
        on a NPC (Weakness, Languid Pace, etc..)</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>NPC</strong> - A non-player-character.&nbsp; These are
        all the monsters, guards and merchants under code-control as opposed to a real person
        sitting in front of their PC.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>PP</strong> - Platinum Pieces - The most revered form
        of currency, short of platinum bars *drools*</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Pet </strong>- The sword and shield we summon. &nbsp;
        Also known as animations.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Packet Loss</strong> - What occurs when the hardware
        between Norrath and your house goes haywire.&nbsp; Pressing F11 brings up the gauge.
        &nbsp; If it's anything but green your best to sit down and meditate till it settles.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>OOC - </strong>Out of Character.&nbsp; This is also a
        channel in the game used by typing <em>/ooc &lt;what i want to say here&gt;</em></small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>LOS </strong>- Line of Sight.&nbsp; This refers to
        whether drawing a direct line to your target you can see it.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>PvP </strong>- Player v. Player</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>PK</strong> - Player Killer</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>OOM </strong>- Out of Mana (never a good thing for us)</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>FM - </strong>Full Mana (always a good thing hehe)</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>AFK</strong> - Away From Keyboard (/afk is the
        command)</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>OMW</strong> - On My Way</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Crap</strong> - I just died again and I love it.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Brb</strong> - Be right Back</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Run</strong> - We are out-matched...any attempt to
        continue the fight is a waste of resources and unnecessary down time and possible loss of
        life. I am leaving..you may stay but the odds just took and even larger turn for the worse
        with me gone.&nbsp; You stay you die.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Stop</strong> - I am mezing one and it you continue to
        attack it it will continue to attack back.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Train </strong>- When you are running from a pack of
        monsters they queue up behind you streaming a path of wabnton destruction in their wake.
        &nbsp; This is known as a train, and you as their chosen prey are the Choo-Choo Engine.
        &nbsp; Often Trains occur near zone points as a person flees for safety.&nbsp; As a matter
        of courtesy you should have a hotkey ready that shouts &quot;Train coming to zone!&quot;
        or something similar so that people can be ready to evacuate from their resting point if
        necessary.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Zone </strong>- Can either refer to the area you are
        in (each area is a zone) or the border between areas where one &quot;zones&quot; between
        them.</small></font></li>
      <li><font face='Arial'><small><strong>Kiting - </strong>The practice of casting a DoT on a
        monster and then running out of its reach as it slowly dies.&nbsp; Normally practised by
        druids or shamans with their Spirit of Wolf spell.</small></font></li>
    </ul>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' height='18'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>Where
    are all my spells?</b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='50'><font face='Arial'><small>Animations from level eight and up
    are sold by a vendor on the main floor of High Keep, the castle in HighHold Pass. Enchant
    Metal spells have thus far only been found in the library in the Third Gate of Neriak.
    Enchantment of Light and Enchantment of Brilliance are not yet in the game.&nbsp; The
    spells list keeps a list of locations for these hard spells. &nbsp; </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='15' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>What's
    the difference between Lull and Mesmerize?&nbsp; </b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='66'><font face='Arial'><small>Lull is not a combat spell. Use it
    to keep one or more mobs from activating when you want to pull half a camp instead of the
    whole thing. Once the mob is activated, Lull is useless- that's when you want to use
    Mesmerize, which will cause a mob to stand dazed and helpless until it takes damage.
    (Note: the follow-on damage from DOT spells such as Suffocating Sphere or Choke will break
    the trance.) </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>What's
    the difference between Mesmerize and Memory Blur?</b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='50'><font face='Arial'><small>If it is effective, Mesmerize stuns
    a monster for a short period as described above, and also has a chance of erasing the
    monster's hate list. Memory Blur only wipes out the hate list, but it almost always works,
    unlike Mesmerize which can be resisted. Both spells are very useful when a creature is
    frenzying on a fragile party-member, or when you'd prefer for a normally non-aggressive
    mob to simply wander off. Blurring a normally aggressive mob will not cause it to stop
    attacking altogether, but will cause to reselect its target as if no previous damage had
    been done (i.e. whoever hits it first or hardest from that point on.)</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>What
    can I wear?</b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='50'><font face='Arial'><small>Cloth-family armour, including
    Cloth, Woven, Mesh, Damask, Gossamer and a few others. Some kinds of any-class armours
    including bone and lupine. And robes, both store-bought and dungeon-found.&nbsp; </small></font><p><font
    face='Arial'><small>Enchanters can also obtain the class specific Insidious Armour from
    the Plane of Hate.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>Why
    doesn't my animation listen when I tell it to attack/back off/ whatever?</b> </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Animations do not respond to normal
    pet commands: They're in permanent 'follow me' mode. </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Can
    my animation dual wield?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Yes.&nbsp; After around level 24
    your pets can dual wield.&nbsp; It is best to equip them with 1 store bought dagger.
    &nbsp; You can also buy these from most vendors which sell tiny daggers for summoning.
    &nbsp; </small></font><p><font face='Arial'><small>With Dual Wield, and a speed buff your
    pet's can virtually match a necro pet of the same level for damage.&nbsp; They are still
    very weak on hitpoints though so you should be sure to stun/slow/fear the mobs they come
    up against.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>Why
    are my spells resisted so much?</b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>You're either fighting things that
    are too many levels higher than you, or you're not using Tashan. </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>OK,
    why is my Tashan spell resisted so much?</b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='34'><font face='Arial'><small>You're either fighting things that
    are too many levels higher than you, or you're fighting monsters with a high Poison
    Resistance, such as some poisonous snakes and spiders.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Why
    didn't my spell do anything? </small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><blockquote>
      <p><font face='Arial'><small>This could be caused by:</small></font></p>
    </blockquote>
    <table border='0'>
      <tr>
        <td width='50%' valign='top' align='left'><ul>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>A line of sight problem</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>Fizzle</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>Resist</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>Invalid target</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>It only lasts two seconds (Lull)</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>Interrupted (perhaps because you were still moving when you
            started casting, or you got hit by a monster, or you heard the sound of lightning)</small></font></li>
        </ul>
        </td>
        <td width='50%' valign='top' align='left'><ul>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>+pvp target, -pvp caster</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>Not grouped (Bind)</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>It did work, but lasted under one second (Charm)</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>It's not a combat spell (Lull)</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>It did work, then it just attacked again (Memory Blur)</small></font></li>
          <li><font face='Arial'><small>It did work, but you weren't close enough to get the message
            that it worked</small></font></li>
        </ul>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='19' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>I
    combined a silver bar and a gem, but I didn't get anything magical. Why? Is jewelcraft
    bugged?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>No, only jewellery made from
    enchanted metal bars will create magical jewellery.&nbsp; If you make jewellery from plain
    bars you will still gain skill, but it will be worth less and will not have any bonuses.
    &nbsp; See the <strong><a href='../misc/jewellery/jewel_ow.asp' target='_self'>jewelcraft
    guide</a></strong> for further information. </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Why
    does Suffocating Sphere do so little damage? </small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>You only get a message about the
    initial damage. SS really does around 30 damage over a period of about 15-20 seconds. The
    same goes for other spells in this line. Experiment on yourself to see exactly how much
    damage you are doing. When you get to 12th level, you'll get Choke which does around 85
    damage and has the best mana efficiency of any spell for any class at this level.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='19' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>How
    long does Invisibility last? </strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Anything from 20 seconds to 34
    minutes.&nbsp; You will get a message when it runs out either from normal duration or from
    being detceted and it dropping.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='19' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>I
    get the message &quot;this is trivial for your skill&quot; when making jewellery.&nbsp;
    What does this mean?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>It means you cannot raise any more
    skill making that object.&nbsp; Try a more expensive gem or the next level of metals.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='19' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Do
    weaken and enfeeble stack? </small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='16'><font face='Arial'><small>No.&nbsp; However the spell list
    does show some of the stacking combinations.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Why
    does Whirl Till You Hurl stop so fast?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Any stun effect will instantly
    break whirl.&nbsp; These include and colour flux series or any of our dd's.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>Is
    there a cap on Jewellery Skill?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='16'><font face='Arial'><small>There is a max cap of 200 skill.
    &nbsp; However, there is no &quot;per level&quot; skill.&nbsp; If you were rich enough you
    could have 200 skill and still be level 1.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Where
    can I find all these cool items I see people wearing?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Your best bet is to head on over to
    <strong>EQLizer</strong>.&nbsp; They have the most complete listing of items and locations
    there.&nbsp; You can get to their site from our <a href='../misc/pages/links.asp'><strong>links</strong></a>
    page.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Why
    did my pet just slash itself for 32000 points of damage?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>If you hide, go invisible, or zone
    your pet feels that you have deserted it to a life of loneliness.&nbsp; Heartbroken by
    this act it decides it's better not to live and commits suicide.&nbsp; You can also
    achieve this effect on other NPC's pets once they have died by casting memory-blur or
    enthrall spells on the pet.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Where
    can I buy Tiny Daggers?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Tiny daggers can be bought in most
    Enchanter guilds.&nbsp; You can definitely get them in Erudin, Neriak, Freeport, and
    Ak'anon.&nbsp; They cost around 1 silver each depending upon your Charisma and faction.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Why
    didn't my mem blur work?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Memory Blur doesn't always make a
    monster forget you.&nbsp; If you are still within its frenzy range and it auto's then it
    will jump you again.&nbsp; Also sometimes it takes mroe than one blur to make it
    completely forget you.&nbsp; You can generally tell if a blur has been successful by the
    monster changing the direction it is facing, stopping, or saying something like
    &quot;Hssssst I hate Enchanters like you.&quot;</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Does
    my animation take exp?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Yes when soloing your pet will take
    a chunk of your exp.&nbsp; However it isn't enough to really be a worry.&nbsp; In groups
    pets take almost no exp so you can use them in situations where charm isn't required.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Does
    my charmed NPC pet take exp?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>The answer to this seems to be no.
    &nbsp; I personally haven't noticed any loss in exp gained when an NPC charmed pet is
    helping me solo.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Why
    do monsters jump on me when I cast a DD Spell on them?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Enchanter direct damage spells have
    a built in mega-taunt.&nbsp; Generally if you cast one a monster will always come at you.
    &nbsp; be ready to mesmerise or stun if you use these on larger creatures.&nbsp; Remember
    we are primarily crowd-control experts in a group environment so good use of a DD and
    mesmerise combo works well.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Can
    I stack mesmerise with high forms of it such as Entrance?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>No.&nbsp; They are different types
    of enthralling and cannot be stacked.&nbsp; You must wait for the meserisation to wear
    off.&nbsp; However, rooting the mob while the mesmerisation is in place will give you
    enough time to put longer stuns on them without getting ganged up on.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>I
    play on a PvP server and I can't charm or fear players, Why?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Verant nerfed the Enchanter in
    November of 1999 on PvP servers, and they had this ability removed.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>How
    much mana do I have?</b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Check the <a
    href='../misc/manacalc/default.asp'><strong>mana calculator</strong></a>.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><b>What
    do the Mana Series of spells do? (Thicken Mana, Crystallize Mana, etc.)</b></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>The are 5 spells in this series,
    all of which are Alteration based: </font></small><ul>
      <li><small><font face='Arial'>Thicken Mana (Level 12, 200 Mana)</font></small></li>
      <li><small><font face='Arial'>Crystallize Mana (Level 20, 400 Mana)</font></small></li>
      <li><small><font face='Arial'>Clarify Mana (Level 29, 600 Mana)</font></small></li>
      <li><small><font face='Arial'>Distill Mana (Level 39, 800 Mana)</font></small></li>
      <li><small><font face='Arial'>Purify Mana (Level 49, 1000 Mana). </font></small></li>
    </ul>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>The final three of these spells are currently not in the
    game. The Purify Mana scroll which was once being sold on the vendor in the Ocean of Tears
    shouldn't be available anymore. The final three spells will almost certainly be quest
    based to obtain once implemented.</font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>The spells are the first part of the <b>Item Enchantment</b>
    role that Enchanters have been waiting for since beta. They <b>do not make mana potions</b>.
    Mana potions would be a Shaman Alchemy skill if they were ever introduced. </font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>The spells are used to make some of the components required
    for the actual Enchantments.&nbsp; Vials of Viscous Mana, and the other various items are
    created using poison vials, the spell and appropriate gems.&nbsp; The Level 49 spell will
    cost up to 500pp per cast to create the enchanted component.</font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>At this time the only &quot;Enchanted Item&quot; available to
    make with a product of these spells is Wu's Fighting Gauntlets for Monks.&nbsp; However,
    it is envisaged that more items will be added to the game in coming months.&nbsp; Some may
    use Blacksmithing skill, some may use Tailoring skill, new spells may even be introduced
    where the required component is one of these items produced as a result of these spells.
    &nbsp; Actual implementation is still very unclear.</font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>In summary, the series of spells is by and large useless
    right now, but the framework is there for a full implementation of using the spells once
    the dev team get around to coding the items and trade skills to take advantage of them.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
</table>
